  "text": "To the best of our knowledge, this paper presents the first empirical study of beliefs updating either in a development context or in response to climate forecast information. We conclude that, despite their limited familiarity with computer-based forecasting methods and the existence of competing forecasts based on widely-accepted, indigenous methods, pastoralists who receive external climate forecasts indeed update their rainfall expectations, albeit in ways that suggest a cognitive bias towards optimism. In the systematic optimism they display when interpreting information, east African pastoralists appear remarkably similar to financial analysts on Wall Street (see [CITATION_1] .",
